 ('2979', 'field', '49', 'en_us', ' believe it or not it s school choice season again for new orleans families to help you through the process we ve compiled a list of some of the most common questions we hear about it 1 what is oneapp anyway oneapp is new orleans centralized school enrollment system unlike most cities around the country where your home address determines where your children go to school new orleans allows families to choose their schools if you want your child to attend a public school in orleans parish it s the system you need to use to select your school preferences and submit your application oneapp is operated by enrollnola which is part of the recovery school district see also enrollnola s websiteoneapp basics for parents via nola comoneapp 101 via enrollnolaspanish version of oneapp s informational video 2 so can i apply to any school in new orleans through oneapp no almost every public school in new orleans utilizes oneapp but there are some exceptions audubon charter ben franklin high edward hynes lake forest charter lusher charter new orleans center for creative arts nocca and robert moton charter are not in oneapp if you re interested in these schools you ll need to apply to them separately since they are selective enrollment schools that draw lots of applications every year we d recommend that you apply to a few public schools via oneapp as well private schools including most of new orleans many catholic schools are not in oneapp either the exception here catholic schools that accept louisiana scholarship program vouchers see also how to apply for a non oneapp schoolednavigator s guide to catholic schools in new orleans 3 when do i need to worry about all this sooner than you think the oneapp process starts early about nine months before the start of the school year here are the big dates for 2016 17 application opens november 1 2016early application deadline december 16 2016schools expo 2017 february 4 2017main round application deadline february 24 2017main round results available week of april 10 2017seat acceptance deadline may 12 2017another application round takes place later in the year for families who were not able to participate in the main round or were not assigned a school more on that below you have the best chances of getting into one of your preferred schools if you apply by the main round application deadline though so don t miss it 4 how many schools can i apply for in oneapp oneapp allows families to apply to up to eight participating schools keep in mind that your child will only be accepted to one school from your list and there are no re dos don t include any school you wouldn t be comfortable having your child attend be realistic though if you re applying for one of new orleans most popular schools consider including a backup school that would still be a good fit for your child but sees less demand 5 how do i figure out which schools might be the right fit the downside of having so many choices is that sorting through them isn t always easy enrollnola s school finder tool is a good place to start it allows you to narrow down your options based on things like locations and state letter grades once you have a short list of possibilities we d recommend visiting the schools many offer open houses and talking to other families to get a better feel for them see also 2016 school grades performance scoresednavigator s 2016 adjusted school gradesnew orleans parents guide to public schools 6 my child s already in a school that we like do i still need to participate in oneapp no if your child is happy at their current school you should not submit a oneapp if you do submit a oneapp and they are assigned to a school on that application your child will lose the guarantee on the spot at their current school assignment 7 am i guaranteed to get one of the schools i list unfortunately no it s possible that you may not get any of your choices which could happen if you only indicate one or two very in demand schools for instance in which case you would repeat the process again in the next round for this reason it s a good idea to include a mix of schools but only schools that you would be comfortable with your child attending see also how oneapp works enrollnola video 8 how do i submit an application you can do it online if you prefer you can also visit one of enrollnola s three family resource centers to do it in person in addition to providing free access to computers for families who would like to fill out the application online the resource centers are staffed with school choice advisors who can help answer basic questions you can also get help with general questions by contacting enrollnola at 877 343 4773 9 what if i don t speak english there are spanish and vietnamese versions of oneapp online for families the family resource centers also have access to translators 10 i got started and now i m totally overwhelmed what do i do before you start checking out real estate listings in other parishes take a deep breath oneapp is designed to be easy to use but it s also easy to get confused choosing the right school for your child is a huge responsibility feel free to reach out to us via email at info ednavigator com if you d like to talk to one of our navigators about your options '),
